TY  - JOUR
TI  - More Stochastic Properties of the Klein-Goldberger Model
AU  - Bowden, R. J.
AB  - [The central idea of the business cycle is of a pervasive cyclical movement of economic indicators. This paper shows that the concept of such simultaneous movements can be given a precise meaning by performing a principal component analysis of spectral density matrices or, with a different shade of meaning, coherence matrices. It suggests also a new method of computing spectral approximations for models that are nonlinear in their variables. The methods are applied to the Klein-Goldberger model for the United States.]
C1  - Full publication date: Jan., 1972
DB  - JSTOR
DO  - 10.2307/1909723
